    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing mandatory IE in M3AP successful outcome messages\n\n### Summary\nThe M3AP implementation was missing the `m3ap_generate_successfull_outcome` function which is required for generating successful outcome messages. Additionally, there was a bug in the `m3ap_generate_unsuccessfull_outcome` function where it was incorrectly using successful outcome fields instead of unsuccessful outcome fields.\n\nThis caused outgoing M3AP signaling messages to be malformed, missing mandatory information elements, and resulted in connection failures during M3 setup procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_common.c`: \n  * Added the missing `m3ap_generate_successfull_outcome` function implementation\n  * Fixed bug in `m3ap_generate_unsuccessfull_outcome` by correcting field references from `successfulOutcome` to `unsuccessfulOutcome`\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Attempt to establish an M3 connection between MME and MCE\n2. Observe that M3 Setup Response messages fail to generate properly\n3. Check that the system cannot process successful outcome messages from MCE\n4. Notice segmentation faults or assertion failures when trying to send M3AP successful outcome messages\n\nThe issue manifests as failed M3 setup procedures and inability to process MBMS session management responses from the MCE.\n"
}